  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.32,
      531.31,
      550.19,
      610.03
    ],
    "text": "Issued at 2.00 p.m. on 05 May 2026 The Intertropical Convergence Zone (where winds from the Northern Hemisphere and Southern Hemisphere converge) affects the island\u2019s weather. As a result, an increase in rainfall is expected over the island from tomorrow (06).",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri,Bold",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0,
      12.479999542236328
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.32,
      613.69,
      456.26,
      636.67
    ],
    "text": "Showers or thundershowers will occur at most places of the island after 1.00 pm.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.32,
      640.45,
      550.63,
      680.23
    ],
    "text": "Cloudy skies will prevail over the Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, Southern and Uva provinces and in Ampara district. Morning showers are also expected in these areas.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.32,
      691.3,
      550.7,
      723.82
    ],
    "text": "Heavy falls above 100 mm are likely at some places in Sabaragamuwa, Central and Uva provinces and in Ampara, Batticaloa, Galle, Matara and Polonnaruwa districts.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      0.9599999785423279,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.32,
      727.48,
      550.72,
      767.26
    ],
    "text": "Misty conditions can be expected at some places in Central, Sabaragamuwa and Uva provinces during the early hours of the morning.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      9.0,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
